This project is the backend of a full-stack e-commerce platform, built using Node.js, Express, and MongoDB. The server is designed to be secure, scalable, and high-performance, providing RESTful APIs for authentication, product management, orders, payments, and user interactions.

It works seamlessly with the frontend built in React and Vite to deliver a complete e-commerce experience.

🧰 Tech Stack & Libraries
Core Backend
Node.js – JavaScript runtime for server-side logic
Express 5 – Web framework for building REST APIs
MongoDB + Mongoose – NoSQL database with schema modeling
Security & Middleware
Helmet – Adds HTTP headers for enhanced security
CORS – Handles cross-origin requests
Cookie-Parser – For parsing and managing cookies
Authentication & Authorization
JWT (jsonwebtoken) – Token-based authentication
bcrypt – Secure password hashing
File & Media Handling
Multer – Handling file uploads (product images, user avatars)
Cloudinary – Cloud-based media storage
Email & Notifications
Nodemailer – Sending transactional emails (order confirmation, password reset)
Development Utilities
Nodemon – Auto-restarts server during development
Morgan – HTTP request logger
Environment & Config
dotenv – Managing environment variables securely

🔥 Make sure to create a .env file with following variables -

PORT=
MONGODB_URI=

EMAIL=
EMAIL_PASS=

JSON_WEB_TOKEN_SECRET_KEY=

ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET=
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRY=

REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET=
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRY=

CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME =
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY =
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET =